The brewing of umqombothi, traditional homemade beer, is a longstanding practice in African culture. eNCA’s Lindokuhle Xulu takes a look at how the beer is brewed. Courtesy #DStv403 JOHANNESBURG - The brewing of umqombothi, traditional homemade beer, is a longstanding practice in African culture. Umqombothi is enjoyed at almost every occasion - whether happy or sad - and is known to have quite a kick. Ingredients include maize meal, sorghum malt, yeast and water. READ: Global brewers aim to please African markets But how many people in this modern society can still brew this delicious beverage? Apiwe Nxusani-Mawela is the first black female brewmaster in the country. Watch the video above as she narrates the process of brewing Africa’s original beer - umqombothi.